  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Risk Communication and Community Engagement (RCCE) for Migrant Population at Point of Entry (POEs) and Border Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will support COVID-19 social and behaviour change (SBC) interventions promoting inclusive COVID-19 testing and vaccination campaign targeting the migrant and surrounding populations at 3 points of entry (Chirundu, Beitbridge, Plumtree), border communities and congregation points. The project will alert populations against complacency in line with WHO protocols for prevention and ensure dissemination of information on preventive measures through information education and communication materials and personal protective equipment as well as to ensure coordination of activities with Ministry of Health and Childcare (MOHCC) and partners working under the Risk Communication and Community engagement (RCCE) Pillar, to undermine potential risk created by mobility dynamics during the festive/holiday season in Zimbabwe.</narrative>
  </description>
